MOFA tutorial with BeatAML datasets

Junyan Lu

12/15/2021

Brief description

This dataset is from the BeatAML study: https://www.cancer.gov/about-nci/organization/ccg/blog/2019/beataml, which is very similar to the study of our CLL cohort. Currently, I am using the drug screen, mRNA expression and mutation data from this study. I am also applying for the access to the proteomic data. If I am granted the access, I can perhaps also add the proteomic view here.

Gene expression matrix

Load expression matrix

exprMat <- read_tsv("processed/rna_count_matrix.tsv") %>%
  data.frame() %>% column_to_rownames("Gene_symbol") %>%
  as.matrix()

Remove genes that have very low expression (optional). Only keep genes with median counts > 10

keepGene <- rowMeans(exprMat) > 10
exprMat <- exprMat[keepGene,]

Variance stabilizing transformation

exprMat.vst <- varianceStabilizingTransformation(exprMat, blind=TRUE)
## converting counts to integer mode

Current dimensions

dim(exprMat.vst)
## [1] 19984   494

Only keep top 5000 most variable genes (optional)

sds <- apply(exprMat.vst, 1, sd)
exprMat.filt <- exprMat.vst[order(sds, decreasing = TRUE)[1:5000],]

Prepare MOFA model

Create MOFA object

Generate a long data frame

AML_df <- bind_rows(
  drugMat.filt %>% as_tibble(rownames = "feature") %>% 
    pivot_longer(-feature, names_to = "sample", values_to = "value") %>% 
    mutate(view = "Drugs"),
  exprMat.filt %>% as_tibble(rownames = "feature") %>% 
    pivot_longer(-feature, names_to = "sample", values_to = "value") %>% 
    mutate(view = "mRNA"),
  geneMat %>% as_tibble(rownames = "feature") %>% 
    pivot_longer(-feature, names_to = "sample", values_to = "value") %>% 
    mutate(view = "Mutations"),
)

We would like to keep the samples that have at least two view (optional)

viewSum <- AML_df %>% 
  distinct(sample, view) %>%
  group_by(sample) %>%
  summarise(nView = length(view)) %>%
  filter(nView >=2)

AML_df.filt <- AML_df %>% filter(sample %in% viewSum$sample)

Create MOFA object

MOFAobject <- create_mofa(AML_df.filt)
## Creating MOFA object from a data.frame...
## Warning in .rename_duplicated_features(object): There are duplicated features names across different views. We will add the suffix *_view* only for those features 
##             Example: if you have both TP53 in mRNA and mutation data it will be renamed to TP53_mRNA, TP53_mutation

Train the MOFA model

Prepare MOFA object

MOFAobject <- prepare_mofa(MOFAobject,
  data_options = data_opts,
  model_options = model_opts,
  training_options = train_opts
)
## Checking data options...
## Checking training options...
## Checking model options...

Training

MOFAobject <- run_mofa(MOFAobject)
saveRDS(MOFAobject,"output/mofaAML.rds")
